quizzes.question:
What output results from the following code?
<?php
 $someString = "15";
 $birthyear = 1982;
 echo $someString + $birthyear;
?>

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]PHP Float[/h1]

A [b]float[/b], or floating point number, is a number that includes a decimal point.[code format="php" ]<?php
  $x = 42.168;
?>[/code]
[h2]PHP Boolean[/h2]

A [b]Boolean[/b] represents two possible states: TRUE or FALSE.[code format="php" ]<?php
  $x = true; $y = false;
?>[/code]
[note]Booleans are often used in conditional testing, which will be covered later on in the course.[/note]
Most of the data types can be used in combination with one another. In this example, [b]string[/b] and [b]integer[/b] are put together to determine the sum of two numbers.[code format="php" codeId="465"]<?php
  $str = "10";
  $int = 20;
  $sum = $str + $int;
  echo ($sum);

  // Outputs [b]30[/b]
?>[/code]
[note]PHP automatically converts each variable to the correct data type, according to its value. This is why the variable [b]$str[/b] is treated as a number in the addition.[/note]
